## Dev setup

<!-- The minimal commands to get a fresh clone running. -->

```bash
git clone ...
cd ...
docker compose up -d
docker compose exec server python manage.py migrate
docker compose exec server python manage.py seed_data --days 30
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:3000.

## Required env vars

<!-- Every var the app reads, with a comment. New devs shouldn't have to ask. -->

- `DATABASE_URL` — Postgres connection string
- `REDIS_URL` — Redis connection
- `JWT_SECRET` — sign session tokens (rotate on any leak)
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` — used by `/api/chat`
- `STRIPE_KEY` — payment, prod only

See `.env.example` for the full list with example values.

## Verification commands

<!-- The commands the agent runs to confirm a change is OK before reporting done. -->

```bash
# Frontend
npx tsc --noEmit
npm run lint
npm run build
npm test

# Backend
docker compose exec -T server python manage.py check
docker compose exec -T server ruff check .
docker compose exec -T server pytest
```

